@startuml observer_pattern
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam classBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam classBorderColor #333333
skinparam classFontSize 12

title Observer Pattern — Real-time Collaboration UML Class Diagram

package "Backend Publishers" #D1FAE5 {
  class TripObserver <<Publisher>> {
    Extends Node.js EventEmitter
    __
    Events:
    • TRIP_CREATED
    • TRIP_UPDATED
    • TRIP_DELETED
    • COLLABORATORS_UPDATED
    __
    + emit(event, data)
    + on(event, handler)
  }

  class "Trip Route Handlers" as TripRoutes <<Publisher>> {
    POST /api/trips
    PUT /api/trips/:id
    DELETE /api/trips/:id
    POST /api/trips/:id/collaborators
    POST /api/trips/:id/days/:d/stops
    __
    Emits events on TripObserver
    after every mutation
  }

  class "Budget Route Handlers" as BudgetRoutes <<Publisher>> {
    POST /api/budget/:tripId
    PUT /api/budget/:tripId/:expenseId
    DELETE /api/budget/:tripId/:expenseId
    __
    Writes to Firebase
    budgets/{tripId}/lastUpdate
  }
}

package "Firebase Realtime Database\n(Event Bus / Subject)" #FFF3E0 {
  class "Firebase RTDB" as Firebase <<Subject>> {
    **Paths:**
    • trips/{tripId}
    • budgets/{tripId}/lastUpdate
    • feed/{postId}
    __
    + ref(path) : DatabaseRef
    + set(path, data) : void
    + onValue(ref, callback) : Listener
    + off(ref, event, listener) : void
  }
}

package "Frontend Observers\n(Zustand Stores)" #DBEAFE {
  class tripStore <<Observer>> {
    + subscribeTripUpdates(tripId) : unsubscribe()
    __
    **onValue callback:**
    • Compare updatedAt timestamps (LWW)
    • Update currentTrip if remote is newer
    • Update trips[] array
    __
    Returns cleanup function: off()
  }

  class budgetStore <<Observer>> {
    + subscribeBudgetUpdates(tripId) : unsubscribe()
    __
    **onValue callback:**
    • Re-fetch full budget from API
    • Update expenses[] and summary
    __
    Returns cleanup function: off()
  }

  class authStore <<Observer>> {
    + initialize() : unsubscribe()
    __
    **onAuthStateChanged callback:**
    • Update firebaseUser
    • Set isAuthenticated
    • Fetch user profile if signed in
    __
    Returns cleanup function
  }
}

TripRoutes -down-> TripObserver : emits events
TripObserver -down-> Firebase : writes updated\ntrip document
BudgetRoutes -down-> Firebase : writes\nlastUpdate timestamp

Firebase -down-> tripStore : pushes via\nonValue listener
Firebase -down-> budgetStore : pushes via\nonValue listener
Firebase -down-> authStore : pushes via\nonAuthStateChanged

note right of Firebase
  **Thin event layer:**
  Firebase carries events only.
  MongoDB remains the source
  of truth for all complex queries.
  
  **Conflict resolution:**
  Last-Write-Wins (LWW)
  via updatedAt timestamps.
end note

note bottom of tripStore
  **Lifecycle Management:**
  React components call subscribe
  in useEffect() and invoke the
  returned unsubscribe in cleanup
  to prevent memory leaks.
end note

@enduml
